For TDD on the registration form, here are the accessibility-focused test assertions I'd suggest. These can be verified with the `scraper` crate for HTML parsing:

**First test (suggested starting point):**
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn registration_page_returns_accessible_form() {
    let app = spawn_app().await;
    let response = client.get(&format!("{}/register", app.address))
        .send().await.unwrap();

    assert_eq!(response.status(), 200);
    let body = response.text().await.unwrap();

    // Page structure
    assert!(body.contains("<html lang=\"en\">"));
    assert!(body.contains("Skip to main content"));
    assert!(body.contains("id=\"main-content\""));

    // Form structure
    assert!(body.contains("<h1>"));  // has a heading
    assert!(body.contains("Create account"));  // correct heading text
    assert!(body.contains("method=\"post\""));
    assert!(body.contains("action=\"/register\""));

    // Labels exist for every input
    assert!(body.contains("<label for=\"email\">"));
    assert!(body.contains("<label for=\"password\">"));
    assert!(body.contains("<label for=\"password-confirm\">"));

    // Autocomplete attributes for password managers
    assert!(body.contains("autocomplete=\"email\""));
    assert!(body.contains("autocomplete=\"new-password\""));

    // Error containers with aria-describedby association
    assert!(body.contains("aria-describedby=\"email-error\""));
    assert!(body.contains("id=\"email-error\""));

    // Submit button with action label
    assert!(body.contains("Create account</button>"));

    // Navigation link
    assert!(body.contains("Sign in</a>"));
}
```

After that form renders, the TDD cycle continues with:
1. POST with valid data -> 303 redirect to todo list (user created + auto-logged-in)
2. POST with missing email -> 422 with inline error
3. POST with invalid email -> 422 with inline error  
4. POST with short password -> 422 with inline error
5. POST with mismatched passwords -> 422 with inline error
6. POST with duplicate email -> 422 with generic "something went wrong" message (enumeration prevention)

Each validation error test should verify the error text appears inside the correct `role="alert"` element.

